Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of computing a minimum cut in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The use of graph compression techniques and flow-based local algorithms suggests that the paper is likely to be classified under the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): This sub-category covers research on the design and analysis of algorithms and data structures, which is directly relevant to the problem studied in the paper. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): This sub-category covers research on combinatorics, graph theory, and discrete optimization, which are all relevant to the problem studied in the paper. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): This sub-category covers research on algorithms and data structures for geometric problems, which may be relevant to the graph compression techniques used in the paper. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): This sub-category covers research on numerical algorithms and computational methods, which may be relevant to the flow-based local algorithm used in the paper. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): This sub-category covers research on the complexity of algorithms and computational problems, which may be relevant to the analysis of the running time of the algorithm proposed in the paper.
